While it mentions traditional ML model development, the focus on GenAI tools and frameworks, along with the need to build and maintain production-grade APIs for these models, aligns most closely with the GenAI Engineer profile.

It does not mention any specific generative AI models, frameworks, or techniques, nor does it involve tasks directly related to ML model development or deployment. The mention of 'staying up-to-date with the latest industry trends and emerging technologies' is too general to classify it as an AI-specific role.

While it mentions a 'DevOps mindset' and 'automation tooling', it does not involve the development, fine-tuning, or deployment of AI/ML models, nor does it focus on generative AI technologies. The role appears to be a traditional infrastructure/DevOps focused position, making it fall under the 'Ambiguous' category as per the coding book's definition for non-AI technical roles.
